          _t('Electric Field Lines', 'Field lines start on + charges and end on − charges. Line density represents field strength. Lines never cross. Between parallel plates: uniform field, parallel lines (fringe fields neglected).', 'Students draw field lines that cross; field lines NEVER cross because the field has a unique direction at each point.', 'Sketch field lines for single charges, dipoles, and parallel plate configurations.'),
