          _t('Charging by Conduction and Induction', 'Conduction: direct contact transfers charge; object gains same sign as the charging object. Induction: no contact; charging object attracts opposite charges to near side; ground removes excess; same sign charges remain when ground is removed.', 'Students confuse conduction (contact) with induction (no contact); in induction, the induced charge is opposite to the inducing charge.', 'Describe the steps of charging by induction including grounding and what charge results.'),
